		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kneesmasher&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Here's my two coppers worth.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are going to play in a group almost exculsively, you have a group of friends and you play with them almost all the time, and you want to hack and slash and kill, then they are right, you should run an Ogre, Troll or Barbarian warrior.  A Paladin will never match up to them in combat, ever!  Actually we are not even close.  But if you run a warrior, that is all you will EVER do, hack and slash. You have no options, no tricks up your sleeves (so to speak), you will never root a mob when it runs, you will never cast invisibility to undead and stroll into Unrest unhindered, you will never lay hands at the last second and turn the entire tide of what was just a second before a losing battle, you will never buff yourself, you will never cure someone's disease or poison DOT, you will never blind a mob and send it running, you will never wield The Fiery Defender.  However, you WILL be able to shell out damage like crazy and take a lot of punishment. Casters will love you to be their meat shield.<br><br>It all comes down to what expection you have. While Paladins are primarily tanks, we do other things.  If you want to JUST tank, then a Paladin is not for you and there are better tanks out there. But if you want to have versatility and flexibility, but maintain a descent tank ability, a Paladin is a great way to go!<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Tor